\section{Conclusions}\label{Conclusion}
In this paper, we have investigated the downlink outage performance of $K$-tier HCN networks under general signal propagation models, allowing for the use of general bounded path-loss functions and arbitrary fading distributions.  Tight upper and lower bounds on the outage probability and outage capacity have been obtained for two specific association policies - the generic association policy and the BARSS association policy.  The validity of our analytical results has also been confirmed by simulations.  The proposed approach can be extended to other association policies, and has the potential of understanding the HCN performance and design beyond specific selections of the path-loss model and the fading distribution.  

